post_text: Good morning SD 163 Families. Today marks the first attendance day of the 2020-21 School Year. We realize that all families have not obtained technology. And our staff members will be engaged in remote planning days on Friday, August 21 and Monday, August 24th. Therefore, our teachers have created an excursion for all students. These excursions will include activities that can be completed with or without technology. Your child’s excursion will be posted in three different ways. 1. Via your child’s teachers class Dojo page. 2. All Excursion will be posted on the district website (Reopening School 20-21 and Under the ‘News Section’) 3. Excursions will be sent under the US Postal Service We are excited about a Reimagine 2020-21 School Year. We are looking forward to all students meeting their teachers on Tuesday, August 25. If you have any questions about this communication, please contact your child’s school. We look forward to an awesome school year. Have a great day!

Via your child’s teachers class Dojo page. 2. All Excursion will be posted on the district website (Reopening School 20-21 and Under the ‘News Section’) 3. Excursions will be sent under the US Postal Service We are excited about a Reimagine 2020-21 School Year. We are looking forward to all students meeting their teachers on Tuesday, August 25. If you have any questions about this communication, please contact your child’s school. We look forward to an awesome school year. Have a great day!

post_text: Beginning Monday, June 8, 2020, we will be serving meals on Mondays and Thursdays only at each building from 9:00-11:00 a.m. Meals will be provided in a 5 day meal pack (five breakfast meals and five lunch meals) that are frozen and comes with a mixture of food that families can reheat in the oven or eat cold. Milk will be also be provided. Reheating directions are included with every meal pack for those items that are served hot.
text: Beginning Monday, June 8, 2020, we will be serving meals on Mondays and Thursdays only at each building from 9:00-11:00 a.m. Meals will be provided in a 5 day meal pack (five breakfast meals and five lunch meals) that are frozen and comes with a mixture of food that families can reheat in the oven or eat cold. Milk will be also be provided. Reheating directions are included with every meal pack for those items that are served hot.

post_text: The District has made some changes to our summer meals program. Beginning Monday, June 8, 2020, we will be serving meals on Mondays and Thursdays only at each building from 9:00 a.m. – 11:00 a.m. Meals will be provided in a 5 day meal pack (five breakfast meals and five lunch meals) that are frozen and comes with a mixture of food that families can reheat in the oven or eat cold. Each child in the home up to the age of 18 may receive a meal pack. Milk will be also be provided. Reheating directions are included with every meal pack for those items that are served hot.

Mohawk Title I Parent Meeting
Mrs. Chinn is inviting you to a scheduled Zoom meeting.

post_text:
Message from Ms. Malinis:
Hello to all my friends! I know we are all happy to spend some extra time with our families, but I miss you all so much! I miss our daily hugs, our story times together, riding bikes in the gym, dancing and singing with Jack Hartmann, and working together to be the best class ever! I know each and every day you are continuing to make me proud and I will be so happy to hear about all the fun you had learning with your families! I would LOVE to see some pictures of you working hard at home during this time we aren’t together! Give yourself a big hug from me and remember that I love you all and I hope to see you soon!
Ms. Malinis

post_text:
Message from Ms. Cristelli:
Good morning friends! I wanted to start today by saying how much I miss all of you. I had no idea that after saying goodbye to you last week, I wouldn't see you again for a few weeks. I miss saying Hi to each one of you, but most of all, I miss your hugs and ability to make me laugh without even trying. I love you all and I hope to see each and every one of you very soon.

While working on your at-home learning activities, have fun! Parents: please feel free to send me photos or videos of your child learning at home.
text:
Message from Ms. Cristelli:
Good morning friends! I wanted to start today by saying how much I miss all of you. I had no idea that after saying goodbye to you last week, I wouldn't see you again for a few weeks. I miss saying Hi to each one of you, but most of all, I miss your hugs and ability to make me laugh without even trying. I love you all and I hope to see each and every one of you very soon.

While working on your at-home learning activities, have fun! Parents: please feel free to send me photos or videos of your child learning at home.

post_text:
Message from Mrs. Rowland:
Good morning...

I would love to see my kiddos each and every day,
So please flood my inbox with tons of pictures...what do you say?

I miss your smiling faces and the laughter in your voice,
Not being at school, was neither of our choice.

So keep practicing your colors, numbers and ABCs,
Learning is important...wouldn't you agree?

I hope this time goes by real fast,
Until we all see each other when we meet again in class!

Be safe and miss you all,
Mrs. Rowland

Message from Ms. Elmore:
Good morning to all my friends, this is Ms. Elmore. I was in our class the other day and it was so empty and quiet that I missed all of your conversations with each other. I missed greeting each of you as you came to sign in for the day. I would love for you to write me a Hello Ms. Elmore note and sign it for me. If you and your family have time in your busy I would love a picture of you and your note.

Missing you guys,

Ms. E

post_text:
Message from Ms. Davis:
Good morning! I wish we were together singing our morning meeting songs! I am missing your smiles, fist bumps, high fives, and hugs! I miss watching you play with your friends, learn new things , hearing you sing our learning songs, watching you dance, hearing your laugh, and covering you up at nap time. I hope you are doing your at-home learning activities with a grown up or big brother or sister. Remember it is important to keep learning while we are out of school. You need to keep getting your brain ready for kindergarten! Be a good listener and remember one of our classroom rules...”Always do your best!” Have a great day! Love-Ms.Davis

Michelle Obama Holiday Performance 2019...

We are pleased to share that the Michelle Obama Holiday Program will broadcast at 7 PM and 9 PM every evening between now and the end of February (except Mondays at 7 PM when Village Board Meetings broadcast) on Park Forest cable subscribers access channels Comcast channel 4/AT&T channel 99.

Thank you to the Village of Park Forest for partnering with District 163 to showcase our student’s talents.
